      "content": "Apologies for the goblin misstep! Let's dive into the science of it, shall we? Whole wheat flour contains more nutrients, including bran, which can be a bit rough on the delicate yeast and bacteria in your sourdough starter. However, it also provides a richer environment for them to thrive, as it contains more minerals and vitamins than all-purpose flour. This can sometimes accelerate the growth of your sourdough starter. The gluten content in whole wheat flour is also higher, which can help your starter to develop a stronger structure, much like how a well-knit goblin community can withstand the elements better than a scattered group. So, while all-purpose flour is generally more forgiving for beginners, whole wheat might just be the treasure trove your sourdough starter needs to flourish. Keep nurturing it, and soon enough, you'll have a bubbly, lively starter ready for baking adventures.",
